      • defineNumEntries

        public boolean defineNumEntries
        Define the number of elements at the beginning?

      • adjustNumEntries

        public int adjustNumEntries
        The game define a counter "num entries" at the beginning of each group in the file. This field alter the counter when reading and writing, to adjust the real number of entries in the file. For now, only dbtechtree.dat require this, due to its particular structure. In dbtechtree there is more than one group, and each counter says N, but there are actually N+1 entries (because there's also the "Epoch" entry, which is not counted).

      • minSeq

        public int minSeq
        Min SequenceNumber for defined objects

      • minID

        public int minID
        Min ID for defined objects

      • indexName

        public int indexName
        Index of the field which hold the entry name. It's -1 if entries have no name.

      • indexSequence

        public int indexSequence
        Index of the field which hold the entry sequence number. It's -1 entries have no sequence number.

      • indexID

        public int indexID
        Index of the field which hold the entry ID. It's -1 if entries have no ID.

      • extraField

        public FieldStruct extraField
        This field define the type/size of extra fields, which are all identical (if the entry size can be dynamic). Only dbtechtree.dat and dbevent.dat use this. It's null if not used.

      • fieldStructs

        public FieldStruct[] fieldStructs
        This array define the description/type/size of all fields of a single entry in the file. You can expect the sum of the sizes of these entries must match the size of an entry in the file.

      • newEntryValues

        public java.lang.Object[] newEntryValues
        Default values used by Unknown/New entries.

        public java.util.function.Function<Entry,java.lang.String> nameBuilder
        Optional function to calculate the name

      • defaultColumns

        public int defaultColumns
        Default number of columns for the UI

      • linkFields

        public FieldStruct[] linkFields
        All fields with links

    • Constructor Detail

      • DatStructure

        public DatStructure(java.lang.String name,
                    java.lang.String fileName,
                    boolean defineNumEntries,
                    int adjustNumEntries,
                    int minSeq,
                    int minID,
                    int indexName,
                    int indexSequence,
                    int indexID,
                    int defaultColumns)
        Create a new DatStructure
        Parameters:
        name - Displayed name
        fileName - File name
        defineNumEntries - If true, the file contains the number of entries.
        adjustNumEntries - This is an offset, to adjust the number of entries
        minSeq - Minimum allowed sequence number
        minID - Minimum allowed ID
        indexName - Index of the name (-1 if there's no name)
        indexSequence - Index of the sequence number (-1 if there's no sequence number)
        indexID - Index of the ID (-1 if there's no ID)
        defaultColumns - Default number of columns displayed in the UI.
